n%20southern%20Lebanon%2C%20ostensibly%20run%20by%20a%20Lebanese%20Christian%20faction%20backed%20by%20IDF%20troops.%20The%20zone%20began%20as%20a%20buffer%20to%20keep%20Palestinian%20groups%20in%20Lebanon%20from%20attacking%20border%20communities%20in%20northern%20Israel.%20It%20ended%20as%20a%20quagmire%20that%20led%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20Hezbollah%2C%20a%20constant%20trickle%20of%20killed%20and%20wounded%20soldiers%20in%20casualty-sensitive%20Israel%2C%20and%20the%20frustration%20of%20a%20long%2C%20grinding%20guerrilla%20war%20of%20ambushes%20and%20roadside%20bombs.%20For%20Israelis%2C%20Lebanon%20became%20what%20Vietnam%20and%20Afghanistan%20were%20to%20the%20US%20and%20Soviet%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsrael%20evacuated%20%E2%80%94%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2000%2Fmay%2F24%2Fisraelandthepalestinians.lebanon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretreated%20under%20fire%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20from%20the%20security%20zone%20in%202000.%20Israel%20returned%20in%202006%2C%20when%2030%2C000%20Israeli%20troops%20crossed%20the%20border%20in%20retaliation%20for%20a%20Hezbollah%20ambush%20of%20IDF%20troops%20in%20northern%20Israel.%20The%2034-day%202006%20Israel-Lebanon%20War%20was%20arguably%20the%20nadir%20of%20Israeli%20military%20performance%20(at%20least%20until%20Hamas's%20surprise%20attack%20from%20Gaza%20on%20October%207%2C%202023).%20Israel's%20overconfidence%20that%20airpower%20alone%20could%20defeat%20Hamas%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20clumsy%20and%20ill-prepared%20ground%20campaign%2C%20ended%20in%20a%20draw%20that%20enabled%20Hezbollah%20to%20claim%20victory%20just%20by%20surviving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22As%20Israel's%20prime%20minister%20in%201998%2C%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20vowed%20to%20keep%20troops%20in%20southern%20Lebanon%20%26quot%3Bwhatever%20the%20cost.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fd65899e0c5c2eeeea037e