%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHAT%20WARS%20HAVE%20BEEN%20FOUGHT%20SINCE%20THEN%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201967%2C%20Israel%20made%20a%20pre-emptive%20strike%20on%20Egypt%20and%20Syria%2C%20launching%20the%20Six-Day%20War.%20Israel%20captured%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Arab%20East%20Jerusalem%20from%20Jordan%2C%20the%20Golan%20Heights%20from%20Syria%20and%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula%20and%20Gaza%20Strip%20from%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%201967%20Israeli%20census%20put%20Gaza's%20population%20at%20394%2C000%2C%20at%20least%2060%25%20of%20them%20Palestinian%20refugees%20and%20their%20descendants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201973%2C%20Egypt%20and%20Syria%20attacked%20Israeli%20positions%20along%20the%20Suez%20Canal%20and%20Golan%20Heights%2C%20starting%20the%20Yom%20Kippur%20War.%20Israel%20pushed%20both%20armies%20back%20within%20three%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20invaded%20Lebanon%20in%201982%20and%20thousands%20of%20Palestine%20Liberation%20Organization%20(PLO)%20guerrillas%20under%20Yasser%20Arafat%20were%20evacuated%20by%20sea%20after%20a%2010-week%20siege.%20Israeli%20troops%20pulled%20out%20of%20Lebanon%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202005%2C%20Israel%20withdrew%20settlers%20and%20soldiers%20from%20Gaza.%20Hamas%20won%20parliamentary%20elections%20in%202006%20and%20seized%20full%20control%20of%20Gaza%20in%202007.%20Major%20fighting%20flared%20between%20Israel%20and%20Palestinian%20militants%20in%20Gaza%20in%202006%2C%202008%2C%202012%2C%202014%20and%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202006%2C%20Lebanon's%20Iran-backed%20Hezbollah%20militants%20captured%20two%20Israeli%20soldiers%20in%20the%20border%20region%20and%20Israel%20launched%20military%20action%2C%20triggering%20a%20six-week%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20also%20been%20two%20Palestinian%20intifadas%2C%20or%20uprisings%2C%20from%201987%20to%201993%20and%202000%20to%202005.%20In%20the%20second%2C%20Hamas%20and%20other%20Palestinian%20militant%20groups%20carried%20out%20suicide%20bombings%20in%20Israel%2C%20and%20Israel%20conducted%20tank%20assaults%20and%20airstrikes%20on%20Palestinian%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20there%20have%20been%20several%20rounds%20of%20hostilities%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%2C%20which%20refuses%20to%20recognise%20Israel%20and%20is%20regarded%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20by%20Israel%2C%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20United%20States%20and%20other%20countries.%20Hamas%20says%20its%20armed%20activities%20are%20resistance%20against%20Israeli%20occupation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHAT%20ATTEMPTS%20HAVE%20THERE%20BEEN%20TO%20MAKE%20PEACE%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201979%2C%20Egypt%20became%20the%20first%20Arab%20state%20to%20sign%20a%20peace%20treaty%20with%20Israel%2C%20under%20which%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula%20was%20returned%20to%20Egyptian%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201993%2C%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Yitzhak%20Rabin%20and%20PLO%20leader%20Arafat%20shook%20hands%20on%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%20establishing%20limited%20Palestinian%20autonomy%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza.%20In%201994%2C%20Israel%20signed%20a%20peace%20treaty%20with%20Jordan.%20But%20a%20summit%20six%20years%20later%20attended%20by%20Arafat%2C%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Ehud%20Barak%20and%20U.S.%20President%20Bill%20Clinton%20at%20Camp%20David%20failed%20to%20secure%20a%20final%20peace%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20a%20proposed%20Arab%20League%20plan%20offered%20Israel%20normal%20relations%20with%20all%20Arab%20countries%20in%20return%20for%20a%20full%20withdrawal%20from%20the%20lands%20it%20took%20in%20the%201967%20Middle%20East%20war%2C%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20Palestinian%20state%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bjust%20solution%26quot%3B%20for%20Palestinian%20refugees.%20The%20presentation%20of%20the%20plan%20was%20overshadowed%20by%20Hamas%2C%20which%20blew%20up%20an%20Israeli%20hotel%20full%20of%20Holocaust%20survivors%20during%20a%20Passover%20seder%20meal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20Palestinian-Israeli%20peacemaking%20efforts%20have%20been%20stalled%20since%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20U.S.%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20in%202020%2C%20Israel%20reached%20deals%20known%20as%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20to%20normalise%20ties%20with%20several%20Arab%20states%2C%20including%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20Bahrain%20and%20Morocco.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPalestinians%20stopped%20dealing%20with%20the%20U.S.%20administration%20after%20Trump%20broke%20with%20U.S.%20policy%20by%20recognising%20Jerusalem%20as%20Israel's%20capital.%20The%20Palestinians%20seek%20East%20Jerusalem%20as%20the%20capital%20of%20their%20future%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQatar%20and%20Egypt%20have%20acted%20as%20mediators%20in%20the%20latest%20war%2C%20securing%20a%20truce%20late%20last%20year%20that%20lasted%20seven%20days%2C%20during%20which%20some%20hostages%20held%20by%20Hamas%20were%20exchanged%20for%20prisoners%20held%20by%20Israel%2C%20and%20more%20humanitarian%20aid%20flowed%20into%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHERE%20DO%20PEACE%20EFFORTS%20STAND%20NOW%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMonths%20of%20on-off%20talks%20on%20a%20further%20Gaza%20truce%20have%20so%20far%20proven%20fruitless%2C%20circling%20the%20same%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbove%20all%2C%20Hamas%20says%20it%20will%20free%20its%20remaining%20hostages%20only%20as%20part%20of%20a%20peace%20deal%20that%20ends%20the%20war.%20Israel%20says%20it%20will%20not%20end%20the%20war%20until%20Hamas%20is%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20issues%20holding%20up%20a%20deal%20have%20included%20control%20over%20the%20border%20between%20Gaza%20and%20Egypt%2C%20the%20sequencing%20of%20reciprocal%20steps%20in%20any%20agreement%2C%20the%20number%20and%20identity%20of%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20to%20be%20released%20alongside%20Israeli%20hostages%20and%20free%20movement%20for%20Palestinians%20inside%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EU.S.%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20administration%20has%20sought%20a%20%26quot%3Bgrand%20bargain%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20that%20would%20include%20normalisation%20of%20relations%20between%20Israel%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia.%20Riyadh%20says%20this%20would%20require%20progress%20towards%20creating%20an%20independent%20Palestinian%20state%2C%20which%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20has%20ruled%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHAT%20ARE%20THE%20MAIN%20ISRAELI-PALESTINIAN%20ISSUES%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20two-state%20solution%2C%20Israeli%20settlements%20on%20occupied%20land%2C%20the%20status%20of%20Jerusalem%2C%20agreed%20borders%2C%20and%20the%20fate%20of%20Palestinian%20refugees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo-state%20solution%3A%20An%20agreement%20that%20would%20create%20a%20state%20for%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20alongside%20Israel.%20Netanyahu%20says%20Israel%20must%20have%20security%20control%20over%20all%20land%20west%20of%20the%20Jordan%20River%2C%20which%20would%20preclude%20a%20sovereign%20Palestinian%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESettlements%3A%20Most%20countries%20deem%20Jewish%20settlements%20built%20on%20land%20Israel%20captured%20in%201967%20to%20be%20illegal.%20Israel%20disputes%20this%20and%20cites%20historical%20and%20biblical%20ties%20to%20the%20land.%20Continued%20settlement%20expansion%20is%20among%20the%20most%20contentious%20issues%20between%20Israel%2C%20the%20Palestinians%20and%20the%20international%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJerusalem%3A%20Palestinians%20want%20East%20Jerusalem%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20walled%20Old%20City's%20sites%20sacred%20to%20Muslims%2C%20Jews%20and%20Christians%20alike%2C%20to%20be%20the%20capital%20of%20their%20state.%20Israel%20says%20Jerusalem%20should%20remain%20its%20%26quot%3Bindivisible%20and%20eternal%26quot%3B%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20claim%20to%20Jerusalem's%20eastern%20part%20is%20not%20recognised%20internationally.%20Trump%20recognised%20Jeru